docs.text: close-up thrill-shots such as these seemed to elicit more laughter from the audience rather than genuine fear , which is a pretty good sign that you're not watching the thriller that the director had originally envisioned .

docs.text: rather , you adopt the opinion that the characters are so goofy and so unaware of the trouble that they're in , that you stop caring about who lives , who dies and where the story goes .

docs.text: the four young teenagers who are the potential sacrificial lambs for this movie are helen and barry and julie and ray - two couples and dear friends to one another .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: during the summer just after high school graduation , they take a fateful drive down a dark mountain highway .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: suddenly , without warning , their car hits someone whom the teens presume was killed as a result of that collision .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: fearing jail time and possible manslaughter charges if they confess , they instead decide to dump the body into the ocean and make a pact never to discuss the episode again .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: a year goes by and things among the four friends begin to change .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: relationships fizzle , future dreams crumble , and attitudes change .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but , they can not forget what they did .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and apparently , neither can someone else .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: someone begins to send letters to all four of the teens with the frightening message : " i know what you did last summer . "
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the letter-writer ( a figure in a rubber slicker wielding a large metal hook ) soon makes his presence known and begins to hunt down the four teens .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it's now up to the four of them to try to figure out who the killer is before it's too late .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: while this movie has some nice visually eerie effects , too much of it's impact had to be generated with extreme close-ups , while the level of suspense was choppy at best .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there is so much more that this movie could have been , but decided to give us nothing but cheap thrills .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it could have been a clever whodunit , but discovering who ultimately was the killer made me just shrug my shoulders .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it could have explored the changed friendships after a year of adulthood , but seemed to only include that aspect to add 15 more minutes to the film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it could have given us smarter characters who knew that anytime you're alone and you see shadowy figures moving about , you don't walk towards them yelling " hello " .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: once you yell " hello " , you can expect an extreme close-up , a thunderous sound effect and an eerie sounding musical pulse .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it's difficult to be in suspense when you know what's about to happen .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the only redeeming aspect of the movie is that i now have a neat idea for a halloween costume , but i'm not sure if the local costume store sells rubber slickers and hooks .
docs.label: negative
